### 1.7 Navigational Compasses (Market Indices)
When the news anchors scream, "The Market is up 2% today!", what does that actually mean? They are talking about an Index—a mathematical barometer for the economy.

* The Nifty 50: An index tracking the 50 largest, most important companies in India. It is "Free-Float Market-Cap Weighted." This means massive ships like Reliance have a massive gravitational pull on the index, while the 50th company barely moves it.
* The Sensex: The older, traditional index tracking the top 30 companies on the BSE.
* Sectoral Indices: Specific trackers for different fleets. Nifty IT tracks tech companies. Nifty Bank tracks financial institutions. Often, one sector will be booming while another is crashing.

